1
00:00:49,591 --> 00:00:50,967
It's not plausible,

2
00:00:51,676 --> 00:00:53,053
nor is it possible.

3
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:55,221
I had a feeling,

4
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:57,432
but how are you…

5
00:01:05,273 --> 00:01:06,483
Master.

6
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:02,330
THE WONDERFOOLS

7
00:02:03,623 --> 00:02:08,002
EPISODE 5
ALL WE NEED IS YOU

8
00:02:38,032 --> 00:02:41,703
I told you to find the Child of Eternity,
not to cause trouble.

9
00:02:44,247 --> 00:02:46,416
I merely showed more signs of the end.

10
00:02:46,499 --> 00:02:48,793
To who? Number 3972?

11
00:02:50,086 --> 00:02:51,212
Pal-ho, don't tell me…

12
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:54,632
Are you worried
that he'll find the child first?

13
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:57,552
Shut your mouth
before I hurl you through the ceiling.

14
00:02:57,635 --> 00:02:59,637
What? Do you think I'd just sit back?

15
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:02,182
I told you both
not to use your powers recklessly!

16
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:05,310
I've already told you
we'd be in danger if we get…

17
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:12,108
Even if you get angry, control yourself.

18
00:03:12,650 --> 00:03:14,986
Just until Father finds the cure, okay?

19
00:03:19,115 --> 00:03:20,450
Ho-ran, you too.

20
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:22,827
Stop it and apologize to Pal-ho.

21
00:03:24,954 --> 00:03:25,788
Sorry.

22
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:39,969
Do you think
that bastard will come back to us?

23
00:03:41,387 --> 00:03:43,014
It's not like he has anyone else.

24
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:46,559
Why are you always so lenient
with that jerk?

25
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:50,772
Because he's cute.

26
00:05:03,928 --> 00:05:05,763
It doesn't hurt at all now, does it?

27
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:21,362
Because he smiled.

28
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:24,824
He only smiled…

29
00:05:26,784 --> 00:05:28,077
when he was with me.

30
00:05:46,137 --> 00:05:49,140
How does he have absolutely nothing?

31
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:50,892
Nothing important.

32
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:53,144
Nothing that holds any memories.

33
00:05:53,227 --> 00:05:54,645
This is really it?

34
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:58,024
Maybe it's because
he's only staying here temporarily.

35
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:02,362
Still, don't people usually
at least have a photo?

36
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,531
Unit 203!

37
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:07,116
Being noisy again!

38
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,243
I can hear you dragging your chair!

39
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,294
Chae-ni! I really can't do this by myself!

40
00:06:18,378 --> 00:06:19,253
Help me!

41
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:31,224
What's all this?

42
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:33,476
He's covered in scars, Chae-ni!

43
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:42,276
So,

44
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:44,987
who did you say attacked you guys?

45
00:06:45,905 --> 00:06:48,032
Wunderkinder, yeah.

46
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:49,826
Yes, they were called Wunderkinder.

47
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:51,869
- Wunderkinder?
- Wunderkinder.

48
00:06:52,370 --> 00:06:54,080
Wunderkinder.

49
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,998
That sounds pretty cool.

50
00:06:57,291 --> 00:07:00,711
Then, are we Wunderkinder too?

51
00:07:01,337 --> 00:07:03,256
No, he called us defects.

52
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:06,968
Who are they calling defective?
Unbelievable!

53
00:07:07,468 --> 00:07:10,555
Are they saying
they're industry standard or what?

54
00:07:14,016 --> 00:07:16,269
Anyway, industry standard or defective,

55
00:07:16,769 --> 00:07:18,980
it means experiments were conducted,
doesn't it?

56
00:07:20,648 --> 00:07:24,569
So the reason that pigeon blinked sideways
and the carp winked at me

57
00:07:25,069 --> 00:07:26,737
was their illegal experiments?

58
00:07:28,531 --> 00:07:29,365
Phenol!

59
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:31,117
So they dumped the phenol too?

60
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,869
I don't know.

61
00:07:33,369 --> 00:07:36,289
Anyway, I'm terrified.
We can't even report them to the cops.

62
00:07:40,042 --> 00:07:41,127
Is that so?

63
00:07:41,919 --> 00:07:45,214
And she won't say
what happened at the vacant lot?

64
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:48,384
No, so I'm trying to find out on my own.

65
00:07:48,968 --> 00:07:51,304
Anyway, I'm glad that Chae-ni is safe.

66
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:55,766
Make sure to report straight to me
if anything happens to you.

67
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:58,019
If you smell danger, just back off.

68
00:07:58,102 --> 00:08:00,521
Yes, Grandma. Don't worry.

69
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:44,232
What kind of life

70
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:46,776
have you lived up until now?

71
00:08:56,953 --> 00:08:57,787
Don't…

72
00:08:59,789 --> 00:09:01,791
Don't what? You're filthy.

73
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:06,921
Don't…

74
00:09:10,716 --> 00:09:12,468
A clean freak even in your sleep…

75
00:09:14,595 --> 00:09:15,513
Fine.

76
00:09:15,596 --> 00:09:17,223
I'll get you a wet towel.

77
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:37,827
Don't go,

78
00:09:39,537 --> 00:09:40,580
Mom.

79
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:45,960
You said you didn't have a mom.

80
00:09:51,966 --> 00:09:54,635
I don't have a prickly son
like you either!

81
00:10:00,057 --> 00:10:01,225
I'm scared.

82
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,855
No, don't.

83
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:07,064
One more time!

84
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:08,149
I'm scared.

85
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:09,066
Please stop.

86
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:12,236
- Please, we're here!
- It hurts. Please stop.

87
00:11:12,213 --> 00:11:13,673
A grown man, crying?

88
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:17,927
You may not have a mom,

89
00:11:18,636 --> 00:11:20,179
but you turned out fine.

90
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:33,901
Eunie, hold it!

91
00:11:38,447 --> 00:11:40,366
Are you okay? Did anything happen?

92
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:43,536
What kind of anything?

93
00:11:46,747 --> 00:11:48,916
It's the northern lights.

94
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:52,628
If you mean anything ordinary, no.

95
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:56,006
Anything is anything.
What's anything ordinary?

96
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:57,967
Where are you off to?

97
00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:01,011
I have some business!

98
00:12:01,095 --> 00:12:03,055
Stay home!

99
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,558
That crazy girl.

100
00:12:52,271 --> 00:12:53,689
Make sure you take these.

101
00:13:52,331 --> 00:13:57,127
HERE TO HELP

102
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:03,008
Hey.

103
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:05,511
Those industry standards or Wunderkinder,

104
00:14:05,594 --> 00:14:07,638
can't we just find evidence
and report them?

105
00:14:07,721 --> 00:14:09,557
It wouldn't even be anonymous.

106
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:12,309
No, thanks. What if they retaliate?

107
00:14:12,393 --> 00:14:15,312
But there's no reward money
for anonymous tips!

108
00:14:17,773 --> 00:14:19,525
From what I hear,

109
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:22,862
several reports were made,
but the cops never found anything.

110
00:14:22,945 --> 00:14:24,572
We need to bring them evidence.

111
00:14:24,655 --> 00:14:26,907
And why do we have to be the ones
to do that?

112
00:14:26,991 --> 00:14:29,660
Who else would do it if not us?

113
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:33,080
Have you forgotten?

114
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:34,957
We've got powers.

115
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:35,916
"We"? Please.

116
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,544
What good are powers
if we don't know how to use them?

117
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:43,007
Frankly speaking, how can we be sure
Mr. Oddball will help us?

118
00:14:45,926 --> 00:14:47,887
We'll know if we ask him.

119
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:41,106
We get it, all right?
You're not exactly happy to see us.

120
00:15:41,857 --> 00:15:43,567
Then why did you show up here again?

121
00:15:44,068 --> 00:15:46,487
Because we still like you, Master.

122
00:15:46,987 --> 00:15:48,405
I wouldn't say I like you.

123
00:15:48,489 --> 00:15:51,825
I'd consider this
more of a strategic MOU relationship--

124
00:15:51,909 --> 00:15:54,536
You sure aren't shy
about telling people you like them.

125
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:58,248
I'm not shy if I don't like people either.
Like, "I can't stand you, Mr. Son."

126
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:03,462
I didn't help you because I wanted to.

127
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:06,590
Most people don't bother
if they don't want to help.

128
00:16:06,674 --> 00:16:09,385
But even if you don't want to,
you help in the end.

129
00:16:09,885 --> 00:16:10,928
Know why?

130
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:15,516
Because you're on my side.

131
00:16:15,599 --> 00:16:18,769
Right, Master? You can't deny it now.
You're on our side.

132
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:20,562
Says who?

133
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:23,732
I say you're on my side.
Got a problem with that?

134
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:25,985
You don't have any friends anyway.

135
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:28,404
What's wrong with having
some people in your corner?

136
00:16:28,487 --> 00:16:31,865
- Isn't that right, Kang Ro-bin?
- You only have one friend too.

137
00:16:31,949 --> 00:16:34,618
What do you mean, only one?
I have another right here!

138
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:36,662
Get a grip. You think I'm your friend?

139
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:39,540
Royal Nightmare,
you're complaining about being my friend?

140
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:41,875
Keep pushing me, and--

141
00:16:41,959 --> 00:16:43,752
What are you, a button? Just hurry up.

142
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:45,546
Hey, let go of me!

143
00:16:51,301 --> 00:16:52,261
You smiled…

144
00:16:57,933 --> 00:16:58,767
did you?

145
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:03,981
I'm guessing you have questions.

146
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:06,984
First, Wunderkinder.

147
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:10,988
If you ever meet them, never engage.

148
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:12,614
- Think we'd want to?
- Why not?

149
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:15,075
- If they provoke us first--
- Sure, I've seen them--

150
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:15,993
You'd die.

151
00:17:18,328 --> 00:17:19,329
You're outmatched.

152
00:17:20,205 --> 00:17:21,832
Of course.

153
00:17:21,915 --> 00:17:23,917
The guy I saw the other day went like this

154
00:17:25,002 --> 00:17:26,628
and crushed everything.

155
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:29,214
I guess those kids are pretty violent.

156
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:30,299
Then,

157
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:32,676
you can help us stand a chance.

158
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:36,472
Why is your first thought
to fight someone you don't even know?

159
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:38,599
Well, they threw the first punch.

160
00:17:38,682 --> 00:17:41,143
They threw it at Master, not at us.

161
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:43,854
Which means throwing it at us.
Whose side are you on?

162
00:17:43,937 --> 00:17:46,523
She just wants to beat up
whoever catches her eye.

163
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:48,525
And I think someone just caught my eye.

164
00:17:48,609 --> 00:17:50,903
You cheeky little punk, I swear…

165
00:17:51,445 --> 00:17:52,946
Mr. Son, you gonna smack me?

166
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,031
- Chae-ni.
- Hit me.

167
00:17:54,114 --> 00:17:55,908
- Can you handle the fallout?
- Hold up.

168
00:17:55,991 --> 00:17:58,243
- Can you handle it?
- To this day, I've never ever…

169
00:17:58,327 --> 00:17:59,745
- Not once…
- Chae-ni, please.

170
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:01,121
I've never hit a woman.

171
00:18:01,205 --> 00:18:02,873
- Mr. Son, please.
- Gloves are off.

172
00:18:02,956 --> 00:18:04,708
Hey, stop butting me with your head.

173
00:18:04,792 --> 00:18:05,918
- Not once, but--
- I'll--

174
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:17,012
Find your own secret switch.

175
00:18:17,596 --> 00:18:19,014
When your abilities activate,

176
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:21,475
when your powers disappear,
and any other changes.

177
00:18:21,558 --> 00:18:23,769
If you start by taking note
of the small things,

178
00:18:23,852 --> 00:18:25,562
you'll eventually see a pattern.

179
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:28,482
To find a pattern in a routine,

180
00:18:28,565 --> 00:18:32,236
we'll need a huge amount of data.

181
00:18:32,319 --> 00:18:33,862
Could you two even handle it?

182
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:38,242
What about you, Mr. Son?
You speak as though you can.

183
00:18:40,661 --> 00:18:44,081
I think mine activates
when my heart races,

184
00:18:44,164 --> 00:18:46,500
but not much makes my heart race nowadays.

185
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:48,335
I've been through so much nonsense.

186
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:50,671
Nothing surprises me anymore.

187
00:18:50,754 --> 00:18:52,005
Nothing flusters me.

188
00:18:52,506 --> 00:18:54,842
I'm just so relaxed.

189
00:18:54,925 --> 00:18:56,802
Then, I'd say the next best thing is…

190
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:00,639
Master!

191
00:19:02,766 --> 00:19:03,600
How about running?

192
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:07,062
I've tried running in figures of eight.

193
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:10,691
I was fine, just sweaty.

194
00:19:15,195 --> 00:19:16,530
You have to cry?

195
00:19:16,613 --> 00:19:18,824
- Well, last time--
- Not cry from getting hit.

196
00:19:18,907 --> 00:19:20,659
- I don't think that's it.
- Guess not.

197
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:24,955
I think my powers mostly activated
when I was with Mr. Son and Chae-ni.

198
00:19:25,038 --> 00:19:27,499
I'm telling you,
you need to be moved to tears.

199
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:29,543
I've graced Kang Ro-bin

200
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:33,172
with countless nuggets of wisdom
to live by, you know?

201
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:36,258
Try it.

202
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:39,261
You want me to do it now?

203
00:19:41,805 --> 00:19:43,807
How should I move him to tears?

204
00:19:47,561 --> 00:19:50,606
Word of advice from a wise man
who's lived longer than you.

205
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:51,857
Sure.

206
00:19:52,816 --> 00:19:54,443
Don't live your life like that.

207
00:19:55,194 --> 00:19:58,113
Neither you nor Eun Chae-ni
have any vigor for life.

208
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:02,451
Do the words "improvement" and "growth"
not exist in your vocabulary?

209
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:03,744
Don't live like that.

210
00:20:03,827 --> 00:20:06,455
Without passion, life is just idling.

211
00:20:06,538 --> 00:20:08,665
Wanna peel onions all your life?

212
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:11,168
That's it, yes.

213
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:13,503
So? Do you feel moved?

214
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:14,838
Yes, I'm annoyed.

215
00:20:14,922 --> 00:20:17,674
Hey, why are you annoyed
by an elder's sound advice?

216
00:20:17,758 --> 00:20:19,968
Sit. You're pissing me off
for no reason again.

217
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:22,888
You think I'm a schmuck
because I hang out with you?

218
00:20:22,971 --> 00:20:26,892
Didn't I tell you I came first in Haeseong
in the National Academic Achievement Test?

219
00:20:27,517 --> 00:20:28,560
Then again,

220
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:31,980
what would you two know about
the noble meaning of academic achievement?

221
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:35,359
What would you know about
being ranked first in Haeseong?

222
00:20:35,442 --> 00:20:38,946
Going on about, "There's more to life
than grades," blah, blah, blah.

223
00:20:39,029 --> 00:20:41,740
A life of whining and excuses,
absent of any reflecting,

224
00:20:41,823 --> 00:20:44,493
is like putting your car in reverse
and flooring it.

225
00:20:44,576 --> 00:20:45,953
Reversing your whole life.

226
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:47,537
You already live recklessly.

227
00:20:47,621 --> 00:20:49,289
How much further can you retreat?

228
00:20:49,373 --> 00:20:50,958
Your back's against the wall.

229
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:52,793
Wait. Let go, Mr. Kang Ro-bin. Wait.

230
00:20:52,876 --> 00:20:53,919
Mr. Kang Ro-bin.

231
00:20:54,002 --> 00:20:55,337
Let go, please.

232
00:20:55,420 --> 00:20:57,047
Let go of me, you bastard!

233
00:20:58,006 --> 00:20:59,716
He's moved. This is how you're moved?

234
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:02,135
Hey, Ro-bin.

235
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:03,971
What's happening? I can't relax.

236
00:21:04,554 --> 00:21:07,266
- You'll break his hand.
- I can't let go. I'm sorry.

237
00:21:09,977 --> 00:21:11,478
Mr. Kang Ro-bin.

238
00:21:11,561 --> 00:21:13,397
Hey, get my hand off.

239
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,564
Get it off!

240
00:21:16,483 --> 00:21:18,068
What's up with them?

241
00:21:18,151 --> 00:21:19,611
Let go!

242
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:23,282
Oh my.

243
00:21:23,782 --> 00:21:26,743
My goodness,
why is there a bunny tail on her butt?

244
00:21:27,786 --> 00:21:28,620
Oh my.

245
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:31,999
Huge.

246
00:21:33,583 --> 00:21:35,002
How unsightly.

247
00:21:36,461 --> 00:21:39,881
Well, they're not leaving much
to the imagination,

248
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:41,925
so it's not thrilling at all.

249
00:21:42,676 --> 00:21:43,510
Oh my.

250
00:21:44,761 --> 00:21:46,555
Oh my.

251
00:21:47,597 --> 00:21:50,142
Hey, get my hand off, seriously!

252
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:53,437
Cockroach!

253
00:21:54,313 --> 00:21:56,148
- Cockroach? Where?
- Where?

254
00:21:56,648 --> 00:21:58,692
Cockroach.

255
00:21:58,775 --> 00:22:01,361
Where is it? Where?

256
00:22:01,445 --> 00:22:03,864
Okay, I've never ranked first place
in anything!

257
00:22:07,159 --> 00:22:08,493
- Cockroach.
- Where is it?

258
00:22:12,873 --> 00:22:15,250
Calm down. Where is it?

259
00:22:15,334 --> 00:22:16,501
Where?

260
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:46,406
What's so funny?

261
00:22:48,784 --> 00:22:51,787
What are you doing there
with those people?

262
00:22:55,791 --> 00:22:58,210
Hey, calm down. Where is it?

263
00:23:01,338 --> 00:23:02,547
It's gone again.

264
00:23:13,975 --> 00:23:15,018
No!

265
00:23:16,812 --> 00:23:19,106
Hey, Master, do something.

266
00:23:19,189 --> 00:23:21,650
There are too many cockroaches.

267
00:23:39,126 --> 00:23:40,877
Why are you back in Haeseong?

268
00:23:42,379 --> 00:23:44,131
To also find the Child of Eternity?

269
00:23:45,340 --> 00:23:46,174
Seok Ho-ran?

270
00:23:47,759 --> 00:23:48,718
Tell me.

271
00:23:50,011 --> 00:23:53,682
What are you doing here with those losers?
Why are you avoiding us?

272
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:56,059
Our views are different now.

273
00:23:56,852 --> 00:23:57,811
And so are our paths.

274
00:23:58,437 --> 00:23:59,980
Are you mad because of Pal-ho?

275
00:24:00,981 --> 00:24:01,898
Why are you there

276
00:24:02,816 --> 00:24:04,151
with those people?

277
00:24:04,234 --> 00:24:05,986
Because they're family.

278
00:24:06,778 --> 00:24:09,281
Can't you tell
by how Father came back for us?

279
00:24:10,157 --> 00:24:10,991
Do you

280
00:24:12,576 --> 00:24:14,744
still call that man Father?

281
00:24:14,828 --> 00:24:17,080
Father still loves us.

282
00:24:17,164 --> 00:24:19,291
He experimented on us and used us.

283
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:21,501
Out of need, not love.

284
00:24:21,585 --> 00:24:25,422
He said he'd make us better. That's why
he's searching for the Child of Eternity.

285
00:24:29,134 --> 00:24:30,635
Is that what you want to believe?

286
00:24:32,888 --> 00:24:34,306
Then keep living that way.

287
00:24:36,016 --> 00:24:39,478
Do you think you're something
after playing teacher to a few idiots?

288
00:24:40,061 --> 00:24:41,897
You don't have a clue!

289
00:24:45,066 --> 00:24:47,277
I made her up, you know.

290
00:24:48,236 --> 00:24:49,988
The mom you saw in your dreams.

291
00:24:50,572 --> 00:24:53,533
Every night, you kept crying,
calling for your mom,

292
00:24:53,617 --> 00:24:55,994
so I felt bad for you. Pitied you!

293
00:24:56,077 --> 00:24:58,163
I'm the one who was there to comfort you.

294
00:25:00,415 --> 00:25:01,625
But you're walking away?

295
00:25:01,708 --> 00:25:03,835
You want to stay with those losers?

296
00:25:03,919 --> 00:25:06,755
You'll die if you do.
Are you okay with that?

297
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:14,387
Yeah.

298
00:25:24,564 --> 00:25:27,317
How can this be happening?

299
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,693
A giant cockroach!

300
00:25:32,155 --> 00:25:33,073
Cockroach!

301
00:25:39,496 --> 00:25:41,706
Die, you bastard!

302
00:25:56,805 --> 00:25:58,473
Master! Are you okay?

303
00:25:58,557 --> 00:25:59,891
Where did the cockroaches go?

304
00:26:01,226 --> 00:26:02,227
What on earth…

305
00:26:03,019 --> 00:26:04,980
Where did the cockroaches go?

306
00:26:05,981 --> 00:26:07,274
The cockroaches…

307
00:26:23,915 --> 00:26:25,333
A Wunderkinder did it?

308
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:30,046
Why did she come all the way there?

309
00:26:30,547 --> 00:26:32,465
Maybe she was bored and came to play.

310
00:26:35,510 --> 00:26:37,971
She came to see
if I found the Child of Eternity.

311
00:26:39,055 --> 00:26:40,223
The Child of Eternity?

312
00:26:41,558 --> 00:26:43,476
The only successful Wunderkinder.

313
00:26:44,019 --> 00:26:47,689
The child doesn't die…
because their heart doesn't stop.

314
00:26:49,274 --> 00:26:51,151
What an amazing heart they've got.

315
00:26:52,861 --> 00:26:56,072
I wanted to find the child first
before those guys did.

316
00:26:57,490 --> 00:26:58,325
But

317
00:26:59,743 --> 00:27:02,245
I'm not sure if finding them
is the right thing to do.

318
00:27:03,330 --> 00:27:06,041
I wonder if I'm exposing them
to more danger.

319
00:27:07,208 --> 00:27:09,961
Maybe I should have just let them
live in hiding.

320
00:27:10,045 --> 00:27:12,672
Well, first things first,
find that friend of yours

321
00:27:12,756 --> 00:27:14,341
and ask them yourself.

322
00:27:14,424 --> 00:27:17,177
"Would you like me
to find you or not find you?"

323
00:27:19,596 --> 00:27:21,973
Since I've had no luck
despite searching so hard,

324
00:27:22,474 --> 00:27:24,434
I'm starting to think
they're already dead.

325
00:27:26,853 --> 00:27:30,398
Didn't you say just two minutes ago
that they can't die?

326
00:27:34,527 --> 00:27:36,988
To be precise,
it's not that they can't die.

327
00:27:38,031 --> 00:27:39,741
They die and come back to life.

328
00:27:41,159 --> 00:27:42,285
Like you, Ms. Chae-ni.

329
00:27:44,913 --> 00:27:47,540
But I'm just a half-dried squid.

330
00:27:48,124 --> 00:27:49,751
I only half-die.

331
00:27:50,335 --> 00:27:53,588
Back then,
your heart definitely stopped beating.

332
00:27:54,339 --> 00:27:55,423
Then it beat again.

333
00:27:57,342 --> 00:27:59,386
So it wasn't a near-death experience?

334
00:28:01,012 --> 00:28:02,514
I actually died?

335
00:28:04,182 --> 00:28:06,351
To be honest,
I was a bit suspicious at first.

336
00:28:07,519 --> 00:28:09,187
I wondered if that heart

337
00:28:09,813 --> 00:28:11,731
had gone to you, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.

338
00:28:12,941 --> 00:28:13,900
But…

339
00:28:14,776 --> 00:28:17,946
But how could I have
the heart of someone who never dies?

340
00:28:19,698 --> 00:28:21,449
If the heart was transplanted,

341
00:28:22,617 --> 00:28:23,702
it could be possible.

342
00:28:23,785 --> 00:28:24,828
Goodness me.

343
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:27,914
You're actually being serious right now.

344
00:28:30,166 --> 00:28:31,292
Come on.

345
00:28:31,376 --> 00:28:35,839
Do I look like someone who would steal
the heart of a total stranger?

346
00:28:36,339 --> 00:28:39,175
Seriously? That's outrageous.

347
00:28:41,010 --> 00:28:42,595
Since your grandmother

348
00:28:43,847 --> 00:28:45,849
sponsored those experiments 20 years ago…

349
00:28:48,810 --> 00:28:52,981
I thought for a moment
something like that could have happened.

350
00:28:56,484 --> 00:28:57,986
If not, I apologize

351
00:28:58,486 --> 00:28:59,988
for suspecting you.

352
00:29:03,158 --> 00:29:04,200
Just now…

353
00:29:04,701 --> 00:29:05,952
What did you…

354
00:29:06,619 --> 00:29:08,121
What did you say

355
00:29:08,955 --> 00:29:10,081
my grandma did?

356
00:29:11,875 --> 00:29:13,126
The person

357
00:29:14,169 --> 00:29:16,713
who sponsored
Dr. Ha Won-do's experiments 20 years ago…

358
00:29:18,965 --> 00:29:20,508
was King Jeon-bok of Myeong-dong.

359
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:30,185
Aren't you overcooking them?

360
00:29:30,268 --> 00:29:32,145
- Should I turn it off?
- Turn it off, kid.

361
00:29:32,937 --> 00:29:35,690
Here, eat first. Have some ramyeon first.

362
00:29:35,774 --> 00:29:38,067
Let's eat.

363
00:29:43,198 --> 00:29:44,824
- Guess they're gone, huh?
- Yeah.

364
00:29:44,908 --> 00:29:46,075
- Let's eat.
- Okay.

365
00:29:53,875 --> 00:29:55,460
Did you not put in the noodles?

366
00:30:07,722 --> 00:30:10,016
You're home? What about dinner?

367
00:30:11,684 --> 00:30:13,269
Why are you just standing there?

368
00:30:13,978 --> 00:30:15,063
Grandma.

369
00:30:16,731 --> 00:30:18,316
What kind of surgery did I get?

370
00:30:23,112 --> 00:30:25,865
It was just a normal heart surgery, right?

371
00:30:26,366 --> 00:30:27,200
Right?

372
00:30:28,576 --> 00:30:29,744
Why are you

373
00:30:30,662 --> 00:30:32,247
asking all of a sudden?

374
00:30:36,876 --> 00:30:38,044
Because…

375
00:30:42,715 --> 00:30:43,758
Grandma.

376
00:30:45,093 --> 00:30:46,553
Listen and don't be shocked.

377
00:30:47,804 --> 00:30:48,805
I…

378
00:30:50,682 --> 00:30:51,516
died.

379
00:30:54,686 --> 00:30:56,771
But I came back to life.

380
00:30:58,606 --> 00:31:00,358
I thought I'd just dozed off,

381
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:01,943
but that wasn't it.

382
00:31:03,361 --> 00:31:04,779
I died and came back to life.

383
00:31:08,867 --> 00:31:10,118
Why am I like this?

384
00:31:12,036 --> 00:31:12,996
Grandma.

385
00:31:14,414 --> 00:31:16,541
The surgery I had when I was seven…

386
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:19,711
What was it?

387
00:31:34,684 --> 00:31:38,313
TOTAL REGENERATION OF PHYSICAL WOUNDS
REVIVES AFTER DEATH

388
00:31:49,073 --> 00:31:51,492
Okay. Three, two, one.

389
00:31:52,410 --> 00:31:53,786
Is anyone there?

390
00:31:53,870 --> 00:31:56,205
- Three, two, one.
- Coming through!

391
00:31:59,292 --> 00:32:00,710
Three, two, one!

392
00:32:27,654 --> 00:32:28,905
Was he dead?

393
00:32:31,699 --> 00:32:32,659
No.

394
00:32:57,642 --> 00:32:58,810
He was killed

395
00:32:59,936 --> 00:33:01,354
for his own sake.

396
00:33:01,896 --> 00:33:05,692
Over half of his brain was lost,
so he can't be revived anyway.

397
00:33:06,234 --> 00:33:09,821
Damage can be repaired,
but lost brain tissue can't be recovered.

398
00:33:10,738 --> 00:33:13,574
We need to transplant that heart
into someone else.

399
00:33:16,703 --> 00:33:18,413
It would be for the child's sake.

400
00:33:20,289 --> 00:33:22,583
We can't leave him like that forever.

401
00:33:45,982 --> 00:33:47,483
Three, two, one.

402
00:34:08,254 --> 00:34:09,088
Scalpel.

403
00:34:47,293 --> 00:34:49,253
HAESEONG DAILY
OCTOBER 1-31, 1979

404
00:34:57,929 --> 00:34:59,889
FIRE AT ORPHANAGE IN HAESEONG

405
00:35:04,769 --> 00:35:07,563
OVER 100 CHILDREN CONFINED
AT LEAST 50 PRESUMED DEAD

406
00:35:10,733 --> 00:35:12,777
THE UGLY TRUTH BEHIND DR. HA WON-DO

407
00:35:49,105 --> 00:35:50,815
I'm sorry.

408
00:35:51,607 --> 00:35:52,567
I'm sorry.

409
00:36:05,246 --> 00:36:06,372
I'm sorry.

410
00:36:24,265 --> 00:36:25,725
I'm sorry.

411
00:36:26,392 --> 00:36:27,518
I'm sorry.

412
00:36:28,895 --> 00:36:32,523
What happened to Master was all my fault.

413
00:36:34,358 --> 00:36:36,569
I'm so very sorry.

414
00:36:38,571 --> 00:36:40,156
I'm sorry to everyone.

415
00:36:42,116 --> 00:36:43,701
I didn't deserve…

416
00:36:44,911 --> 00:36:46,871
All because of me…

417
00:36:49,373 --> 00:36:50,791
I'm sorry.

418
00:38:48,617 --> 00:38:49,660
Should I try

419
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:51,537
talking to Chae-ni?

420
00:38:52,330 --> 00:38:54,206
Whatever you say to her,

421
00:38:54,707 --> 00:38:56,917
she won't be willing to listen.

422
00:39:05,217 --> 00:39:06,177
And you're sure

423
00:39:07,261 --> 00:39:09,180
the blood patch was human blood?

424
00:39:09,889 --> 00:39:10,848
Yes, Grandma.

425
00:39:11,515 --> 00:39:13,893
We'd best dig deeper into this, Jun-mo.

426
00:39:14,393 --> 00:39:16,771
I need to know

427
00:39:17,396 --> 00:39:18,939
what they're up to over there.

428
00:39:23,277 --> 00:39:24,111
Hey.

429
00:39:25,112 --> 00:39:26,405
Doesn't even say hi.

430
00:39:26,906 --> 00:39:27,823
Where's Ms. Chae-ni?

431
00:39:28,407 --> 00:39:29,241
Sorry?

432
00:39:30,034 --> 00:39:30,910
I don't know.

433
00:39:30,993 --> 00:39:32,870
She won't reply when I talk to her.

434
00:39:32,953 --> 00:39:34,872
She just lies there with her back turned.

435
00:39:35,915 --> 00:39:38,000
Can't you bump up our hourly rate?

436
00:39:38,084 --> 00:39:42,171
My Mi-hui keeps telling me to scrap
my sense of duty and just deliver flowers.

437
00:39:42,254 --> 00:39:44,882
So Ms. Eun Chae-ni has been home
the entire time?

438
00:39:44,965 --> 00:39:45,966
Yes.

439
00:39:46,592 --> 00:39:49,845
Except she's doing all that
at my place, not hers.

440
00:39:49,929 --> 00:39:52,223
Honestly, what's gotten into her?

441
00:39:52,723 --> 00:39:53,933
Did you hear me or what?

442
00:39:54,517 --> 00:39:55,684
Hey, you!

443
00:39:56,894 --> 00:40:00,106
Goddammit, what the hell did you eat?

444
00:40:16,122 --> 00:40:18,999
HAESEONG MILLENNIUM FIREWORKS FESTIVAL
DECEMBER 31, 1999

445
00:40:28,717 --> 00:40:31,554
Master! Here, bungeo-ppang.

446
00:40:32,721 --> 00:40:33,556
Here, they're hot.

447
00:40:33,639 --> 00:40:34,598
It's hot.

448
00:40:35,099 --> 00:40:37,351
Miracles shall come to those who believe.

449
00:40:42,314 --> 00:40:47,069
The marked one who will lead us
to salvation and eternal life,

450
00:40:47,153 --> 00:40:50,990
our shepherd Kim Pal-ho,
will now deliver his sermon!

451
00:41:11,969 --> 00:41:13,888
- One, two!
- Taekwon!

452
00:41:13,971 --> 00:41:14,930
Have a nice day.

453
00:41:15,014 --> 00:41:21,270
- One, two!
- Taekwon!

454
00:41:21,353 --> 00:41:24,440
- One, two!
- Taekwon!

455
00:41:27,526 --> 00:41:30,446
Come to the fireworks festival. Hello.

456
00:41:30,529 --> 00:41:31,906
Hello.

457
00:41:36,035 --> 00:41:38,454
Hurry up and hand them out
so we can get home!

458
00:41:38,537 --> 00:41:40,623
I can't separate them with these on.

459
00:41:40,706 --> 00:41:42,249
Then take your gloves off.

460
00:43:15,384 --> 00:43:16,302
Do you want some?

461
00:43:34,653 --> 00:43:36,238
That'll be 1,250 won.

462
00:43:48,667 --> 00:43:50,169
I thought long and hard,

463
00:43:50,669 --> 00:43:52,379
but I just couldn't figure out

464
00:43:53,130 --> 00:43:55,257
what to do in a situation like this.

465
00:43:57,843 --> 00:44:01,764
My grandma is the wisest,
most upright person

466
00:44:02,264 --> 00:44:03,974
in the world.

467
00:44:05,726 --> 00:44:08,062
But for her to have done
something like that…

468
00:44:10,147 --> 00:44:12,024
All because of me.

469
00:44:14,902 --> 00:44:16,612
I considered turning a blind eye,

470
00:44:17,321 --> 00:44:18,947
pretending I had no clue

471
00:44:20,240 --> 00:44:22,618
and acting like nothing happened.

472
00:44:24,787 --> 00:44:25,996
But

473
00:44:26,664 --> 00:44:29,333
that wouldn't mean anything actually did.

474
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:35,339
That heart became my heart,

475
00:44:36,590 --> 00:44:39,301
and here I am, alive and well.

476
00:44:43,931 --> 00:44:45,891
I never chose

477
00:44:47,309 --> 00:44:48,769
to live the way I am.

478
00:44:51,230 --> 00:44:53,399
Just like you didn't choose

479
00:44:54,274 --> 00:44:55,818
to be the way you are.

480
00:44:58,362 --> 00:45:00,739
So don't think too hard about it.

481
00:45:01,657 --> 00:45:02,866
I know from experience

482
00:45:04,118 --> 00:45:06,453
that it doesn't help you
find the right answer.

483
00:45:09,289 --> 00:45:10,666
What should I do, then?

484
00:45:15,879 --> 00:45:17,506
You won't be able to meet

485
00:45:18,966 --> 00:45:20,759
that friend of yours.

486
00:45:29,601 --> 00:45:30,936
I'm sorry.

487
00:45:39,987 --> 00:45:41,488
Hey, Chae-ni!

488
00:45:45,617 --> 00:45:46,452
These.

489
00:45:49,621 --> 00:45:51,123
Chae-ni.

490
00:45:51,206 --> 00:45:54,460
Your grandma told me
to make sure you eat all of this.

491
00:45:55,169 --> 00:45:56,503
I told her,

492
00:45:56,587 --> 00:45:59,631
"Since you're here, why don't you
at least see her before you go?"

493
00:45:59,715 --> 00:46:03,719
But she said, "No. As long as my Eunie
is doing well, that's all that matters."

494
00:46:03,802 --> 00:46:04,970
You should…

495
00:46:21,904 --> 00:46:22,905
Chae-ni.

496
00:46:43,592 --> 00:46:46,386
Because I have so many sins,

497
00:46:47,721 --> 00:46:49,765
because my sins are so great…

498
00:46:53,519 --> 00:46:56,814
I made my baby go through so much pain.

499
00:47:27,177 --> 00:47:29,304
I can't condone what you did, Grandma,

500
00:47:30,764 --> 00:47:33,100
because what you did was truly terrible.

501
00:47:34,601 --> 00:47:35,519
Right.

502
00:47:40,274 --> 00:47:41,984
I don't expect you to.

503
00:47:42,067 --> 00:47:43,360
But I can…

504
00:47:45,654 --> 00:47:47,406
stand with you if people throw stones.

505
00:47:47,489 --> 00:47:48,657
Right.

506
00:47:51,952 --> 00:47:54,079
We can atone for your sins

507
00:47:54,663 --> 00:47:56,790
and beg for forgiveness together.

508
00:47:58,250 --> 00:47:59,710
It's only natural.

509
00:48:03,505 --> 00:48:04,339
Right.

510
00:48:05,090 --> 00:48:06,258
So, from now on,

511
00:48:07,009 --> 00:48:08,552
I'll try to live life…

512
00:48:11,013 --> 00:48:12,306
to the fullest.

513
00:48:14,600 --> 00:48:15,976
If I don't,

514
00:48:17,019 --> 00:48:18,645
I think I'll feel guilty

515
00:48:19,605 --> 00:48:21,440
toward the owner of my heart

516
00:48:22,024 --> 00:48:23,650
and the other kids.

517
00:48:26,403 --> 00:48:27,237
Right.

518
00:48:28,989 --> 00:48:29,990
So…

519
00:48:32,951 --> 00:48:34,453
I need a little time.

520
00:48:40,959 --> 00:48:42,294
I'm proud of you, my baby.

521
00:48:43,754 --> 00:48:45,881
Did you eat all of this in one day?

522
00:48:45,964 --> 00:48:48,091
You're impressive, as always.

523
00:48:51,219 --> 00:48:53,931
Well, of course.
I hadn't eaten a thing all day.

524
00:48:54,014 --> 00:48:58,101
From now on,
I'm going to live life to the full,

525
00:48:58,644 --> 00:48:59,937
so I can't go hungry.

526
00:49:04,942 --> 00:49:06,944
Sure, giving it your all is great.

527
00:49:07,569 --> 00:49:09,780
But why are you doing that here?

528
00:49:10,906 --> 00:49:13,659
Well, things are still
a little awkward with Grandma.

529
00:49:14,785 --> 00:49:15,661
And what about you?

530
00:49:15,744 --> 00:49:17,079
It's dangerous

531
00:49:17,579 --> 00:49:20,082
for an adult man
and a woman to be alone all night.

532
00:49:20,165 --> 00:49:21,249
You know it.

533
00:49:21,875 --> 00:49:24,169
Dangerous for whom? For me?

534
00:49:26,797 --> 00:49:30,175
Come on. It'll be more fun to train
while living together. Right, Master?

535
00:49:31,468 --> 00:49:32,594
Come lie down here.

536
00:49:37,557 --> 00:49:40,185
You leave tomorrow.
I'm not letting you stay any longer.

537
00:49:56,910 --> 00:50:00,122
Should I be relieved
that Mr. Son isn't here too, at least?

538
00:50:08,922 --> 00:50:12,509
We need a table or something.
Every meal is so uncomfortable.

539
00:50:12,592 --> 00:50:14,052
Thank you for the food.

540
00:50:14,136 --> 00:50:15,178
Dig in.

541
00:50:19,141 --> 00:50:20,475
- It's hot!
- It's hot!

542
00:50:22,227 --> 00:50:23,061
Hello?

543
00:50:23,145 --> 00:50:26,732
I booked a cleaning job at 1:00 p.m.
at the container park. Meet me there.

544
00:50:27,858 --> 00:50:30,068
A training session
disguised as a cleaning job?

545
00:50:30,152 --> 00:50:33,363
Okay, got it.
I'll tell Ro-bin and Mr. Son too.

546
00:50:34,990 --> 00:50:36,074
You're together?

547
00:50:36,950 --> 00:50:37,784
Yes.

548
00:50:38,618 --> 00:50:39,453
Where?

549
00:50:43,957 --> 00:50:47,586
See you later.

550
00:50:48,086 --> 00:50:49,171
You're good at that.

551
00:50:49,963 --> 00:50:53,050
Make sure you hide your stuff well,
especially things like this.

552
00:50:53,133 --> 00:50:55,218
If he finds these,
we'll be caught red-handed.

553
00:50:55,302 --> 00:50:56,303
- Hide them well.
- Okay.

554
00:50:56,386 --> 00:50:57,929
And make sure to do the dishes.

555
00:50:58,013 --> 00:50:59,389
Got it.

556
00:50:59,890 --> 00:51:02,893
We can't leave a single trace.
And let's hurry.

557
00:51:14,071 --> 00:51:15,197
I guess it's true.

558
00:51:15,280 --> 00:51:17,240
It works when my feelings are hurt.

559
00:51:19,159 --> 00:51:21,161
But isn't that too cruel?

560
00:51:21,244 --> 00:51:25,582
Isn't it bad if I need to hear mean things
to activate my powers?

561
00:51:27,584 --> 00:51:30,712
What about you, Mr. Son?
Still don't know your secret switch?

562
00:51:30,796 --> 00:51:33,924
No, I'm not sure yet.

563
00:51:36,259 --> 00:51:37,177
What the…

564
00:51:38,261 --> 00:51:39,096
What was that?

565
00:51:40,639 --> 00:51:42,224
I think you just lied.

566
00:51:42,808 --> 00:51:46,436
Lied? No, I didn't.
What do you mean I lied? I didn't!

567
00:51:46,520 --> 00:51:48,814
This is dusty.
I'd better go shake the dust out.

568
00:51:55,028 --> 00:51:56,113
It's true.

569
00:51:56,613 --> 00:51:57,447
You liar.

570
00:52:05,122 --> 00:52:07,541
Well, aren't you as sharp as a hawk?

571
00:52:11,336 --> 00:52:14,798
Running or being breathless doesn't work,
and you don't even get startled,

572
00:52:14,881 --> 00:52:18,635
so you need to think of other ways,
not just wait around for it to happen.

573
00:52:20,011 --> 00:52:23,181
Find out whether your trigger
is an emotion, a word, or an action.

574
00:52:25,392 --> 00:52:28,687
Wow, Mr. Oddball has quite the temper.

575
00:52:28,770 --> 00:52:30,021
- Excuse me.
- He's cool.

576
00:52:30,105 --> 00:52:31,189
Ms. Eun Chae-ni?

577
00:52:31,815 --> 00:52:32,649
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

578
00:52:32,732 --> 00:52:35,360
For goodness' sake.

579
00:52:35,443 --> 00:52:38,822
So people really do show their true colors
when teaching you to drive.

580
00:52:38,905 --> 00:52:39,906
Why are you so mad?

581
00:52:39,990 --> 00:52:42,701
'Cause instead of trying,
you're just sitting there all anxious.

582
00:52:43,660 --> 00:52:45,036
Man, I'm parched!

583
00:52:51,668 --> 00:52:53,336
Do you think I want to mope around?

584
00:52:53,420 --> 00:52:54,254
Hey!

585
00:52:54,337 --> 00:52:55,714
You can't have caffeine.

586
00:52:57,424 --> 00:52:58,258
Oh, right.

587
00:53:03,555 --> 00:53:04,681
I'm fine.

588
00:53:08,894 --> 00:53:11,354
What the…
Hey, I can hear that from over here.

589
00:53:16,067 --> 00:53:19,779
All across the country we go

590
00:53:19,863 --> 00:53:22,073
Let's go!

591
00:53:22,782 --> 00:53:25,076
- What the heck was that?
- Take the bus, leave Seoul

592
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:27,287
To Gangwon State
Seoraksan, Yangyang, Naksansa

593
00:53:27,370 --> 00:53:29,456
Over Daegwallyeong Pass
Gangneung Gyeongpodae

594
00:53:29,539 --> 00:53:31,124
Samcheok, Chokseokru
Ulleungdo, Seonginbong

595
00:53:31,208 --> 00:53:33,752
- Tired from Taebaeksan
- What the heck?

596
00:53:33,835 --> 00:53:35,420
On to Chungcheong-do

597
00:53:35,503 --> 00:53:38,006
Through the winding islands

598
00:53:38,089 --> 00:53:39,966
Jeju, full of haenyeo

599
00:53:40,050 --> 00:53:42,427
Off to Gyeongsang-do

600
00:53:43,303 --> 00:53:45,472
So much to see in Gyeongju

601
00:53:45,555 --> 00:53:47,766
Bulguksa, Dabotap
Seokgatap, Cheomseongdae

602
00:53:47,849 --> 00:53:49,601
Seokguram, Tohamsan at sunrise

603
00:53:49,684 --> 00:53:51,728
Ulsan factory tours

604
00:53:51,811 --> 00:53:53,813
Pohang Beach, the steel mills

605
00:53:53,897 --> 00:53:55,774
The express bus to Seoul awaits

606
00:53:55,857 --> 00:53:58,109
My legs and back hurt

607
00:53:58,193 --> 00:53:59,861
Oh dear, oh dear

608
00:53:59,945 --> 00:54:02,739
That was a good tour

609
00:54:04,491 --> 00:54:07,661
Good thinking,
buying this wild ginseng wine.

610
00:54:11,373 --> 00:54:14,084
Caffeine… effective.

611
00:54:17,462 --> 00:54:20,340
Get up, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.
Let's move on to the next step.

612
00:54:23,843 --> 00:54:26,930
Get on up, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.
Let's move on to the next step.

613
00:54:28,556 --> 00:54:32,227
Let's see how much caffeine you need
and if you can easily take others along.

614
00:54:32,811 --> 00:54:34,437
If you can hold someone's hand--

615
00:54:39,276 --> 00:54:42,988
Man, my eyes are so dry
from all the wind she's kicking up.

616
00:54:43,613 --> 00:54:46,157
Deary me.

617
00:54:46,241 --> 00:54:48,243
It's so nice and peaceful--

618
00:54:48,743 --> 00:54:49,869
Back already?

619
00:54:50,370 --> 00:54:52,122
Chae-ni, where's Master?

620
00:54:53,999 --> 00:54:55,834
We need to be touching to go together.

621
00:54:56,918 --> 00:54:59,045
Why'd he get so annoyed?
We can just try it.

622
00:54:59,129 --> 00:55:01,339
Okay, and where is Master?

623
00:55:01,423 --> 00:55:04,551
I'm starting to get sick of him.
Should I just leave him there?

624
00:55:04,634 --> 00:55:05,552
What?

625
00:55:10,265 --> 00:55:12,600
- Hello--
- You better not leave me here by myself.

626
00:55:15,353 --> 00:55:16,646
I swear he's inside my--

627
00:55:19,858 --> 00:55:20,775
Got any eye drops?

628
00:55:21,484 --> 00:55:22,319
None.

629
00:55:35,707 --> 00:55:37,042
Hey, Master!

630
00:55:37,542 --> 00:55:38,877
Here!

631
00:55:42,922 --> 00:55:46,259
So I guess we need to be touching
for us to travel together.

632
00:55:46,343 --> 00:55:48,011
Wait there.

633
00:55:48,720 --> 00:55:50,305
Don't go anywhere.

634
00:55:52,140 --> 00:55:53,391
Come here.

635
00:55:53,933 --> 00:55:55,393
Okay!

636
00:56:16,915 --> 00:56:18,958
Master!

637
00:56:27,509 --> 00:56:28,676
Grab on!

638
00:56:44,859 --> 00:56:46,152
Hello?

639
00:56:54,327 --> 00:56:55,370
I'll be right there!

640
00:57:26,067 --> 00:57:28,236
I'll just take an intercity bus.

641
00:57:29,320 --> 00:57:30,196
Go.

642
00:57:30,864 --> 00:57:31,990
Just go.

643
00:57:32,490 --> 00:57:36,786
I guess I don't always land
in the same spot.

644
00:57:37,287 --> 00:57:38,872
It's totally random!

645
00:58:07,275 --> 00:58:08,318
Master!

646
00:58:09,152 --> 00:58:11,154
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

647
00:58:39,974 --> 00:58:43,061
You're really putting me off
working with you. This looks fine.

648
00:58:43,144 --> 00:58:44,646
You talk too much, punk.

649
00:58:45,146 --> 00:58:47,232
Look. It's laid out nicely.

650
00:58:49,359 --> 00:58:51,486
Master! You're back.

651
00:58:51,986 --> 00:58:53,071
That was fast.

652
00:58:58,952 --> 00:59:01,329
What are you doing?

653
00:59:02,163 --> 00:59:05,708
Let's eat together.
Chae-ni's been talking about it for days.

654
00:59:06,668 --> 00:59:07,502
Why?

655
00:59:09,003 --> 00:59:09,837
Your birthday.

656
00:59:10,713 --> 00:59:13,591
It's not any time soon.
And it's not even my real birthday.

657
00:59:15,260 --> 00:59:16,427
A party to celebrate your

658
00:59:17,220 --> 00:59:18,304
two-month pre-birthday.

659
00:59:18,930 --> 00:59:20,223
Who even celebrates that?

660
00:59:21,891 --> 00:59:24,310
Does a party have to be something special?

661
00:59:24,811 --> 00:59:27,355
If we throw one and it's fun,
it's a party.

662
00:59:27,438 --> 00:59:29,232
You can have a party two months before,

663
00:59:29,315 --> 00:59:31,734
one month before,
and on your actual birthday.

664
00:59:32,318 --> 00:59:33,570
Even a month after.

665
00:59:34,404 --> 00:59:35,238
I guess,

666
00:59:36,072 --> 00:59:38,575
if you feel like it,
we could even have one every day.

667
00:59:39,784 --> 00:59:40,618
Why?

668
00:59:41,286 --> 00:59:44,706
We thought you would've eaten alone,
slept alone,

669
00:59:44,789 --> 00:59:48,126
watched TV alone, and so on, Master.

670
00:59:49,127 --> 00:59:50,587
Now we'll do all that with you.

671
00:59:56,217 --> 00:59:59,429
Mr. Son, I thought you would
at least have more sense.

672
01:00:00,346 --> 01:00:02,390
I have plenty of sense.

673
01:00:02,473 --> 01:00:06,185
But Chae-ni said she'd give me her wage,
so I'm attending for business purposes.

674
01:00:06,269 --> 01:00:08,771
I have no personal feelings
about this at all.

675
01:00:09,689 --> 01:00:12,191
I hope that you are never lonely

676
01:00:12,275 --> 01:00:14,611
and wish you a lifetime of happiness.

677
01:00:15,612 --> 01:00:16,946
For you, Master,

678
01:00:17,614 --> 01:00:18,448
and for us.

679
01:00:19,991 --> 01:00:20,825
Yeah.

680
01:00:21,326 --> 01:00:24,120
Starting today, every day.

681
01:00:33,212 --> 01:00:34,464
Hey, what time is it?

682
01:00:34,964 --> 01:00:38,801
The bakery's about to close.
Who's going to go buy the cake?

683
01:00:51,981 --> 01:00:53,733
Why didn't you buy it on your way in?

684
01:00:53,816 --> 01:00:57,403
Goodness, are you a young master
from a rich family?

685
01:00:57,487 --> 01:01:00,031
You have to go near closing time
to get one on clearance.

686
01:01:01,699 --> 01:01:02,825
Wait, did you come

687
01:01:03,660 --> 01:01:04,786
to pick me up?

688
01:01:10,416 --> 01:01:12,794
About your mom, Master.

689
01:01:13,294 --> 01:01:15,588
So she's not dead,
just living away from you?

690
01:01:15,672 --> 01:01:16,923
Where does she live?

691
01:01:17,924 --> 01:01:19,342
Why are you suddenly…

692
01:01:19,842 --> 01:01:21,177
The other day, in your sleep,

693
01:01:22,178 --> 01:01:23,513
you called for your mom.

694
01:01:24,555 --> 01:01:26,391
You cried, "Mom."

695
01:01:28,643 --> 01:01:29,560
Did I?

696
01:01:31,521 --> 01:01:34,232
I don't even know
if those memories are real.

697
01:01:34,732 --> 01:01:36,109
I lost my memories in the lab.

698
01:01:38,319 --> 01:01:41,114
A person who I think is my mom
appears in my dreams sometimes,

699
01:01:41,781 --> 01:01:44,158
but I can't see her face,
and I don't remember her.

700
01:01:45,535 --> 01:01:47,286
I don't even know my real name.

701
01:01:52,583 --> 01:01:54,669
Your face looks like you're thinking,

702
01:01:55,169 --> 01:01:56,713
"That's all my fault too."

703
01:01:58,798 --> 01:02:00,800
You, Master,

704
01:02:01,384 --> 01:02:02,844
and all your friends…

705
01:02:06,931 --> 01:02:09,100
I feel like it's all my fault.

706
01:02:09,183 --> 01:02:10,393
You know…

707
01:02:12,186 --> 01:02:16,315
where, how, and what you'll do,
and who you'll live to protect

708
01:02:16,816 --> 01:02:18,151
are for you to decide.

709
01:02:18,901 --> 01:02:20,278
Not someone else.

710
01:02:23,573 --> 01:02:24,824
Master,

711
01:02:25,491 --> 01:02:27,285
you really do seem like a master.

712
01:02:28,995 --> 01:02:30,788
You have so many teachings.

713
01:02:33,374 --> 01:02:37,044
You leave me with no choice
but to pledge my loyalty to you.

714
01:02:39,297 --> 01:02:42,467
I can't give you all of my life,

715
01:02:42,967 --> 01:02:46,095
but I'll give you about one tenth of it,
out of loyalty.

716
01:02:47,847 --> 01:02:49,891
Don't let people in so easily.

717
01:02:51,350 --> 01:02:53,352
And don't be fooled by shallow kindness.

718
01:02:57,315 --> 01:02:58,983
That way, though you may get lonely,

719
01:02:59,817 --> 01:03:00,860
you're never in danger.

720
01:03:03,988 --> 01:03:06,240
So that's how you've lived your life.

721
01:03:07,700 --> 01:03:10,328
If you still want to let someone in
despite all that,

722
01:03:10,828 --> 01:03:11,829
remember this.

723
01:03:12,955 --> 01:03:14,415
You need the courage to risk…

724
01:03:16,417 --> 01:03:19,045
your whole life, not just one tenth of it.

725
01:03:20,004 --> 01:03:22,173
Being by someone's side

726
01:03:22,673 --> 01:03:26,761
isn't as dangerous or as difficult
as you think.

727
01:03:27,929 --> 01:03:28,930
You just stay.

728
01:03:30,640 --> 01:03:32,183
It's such an easy thing,

729
01:03:32,850 --> 01:03:34,435
so why overcomplicate it?

730
01:03:37,230 --> 01:03:38,064
Because usually…

731
01:03:42,401 --> 01:03:43,611
you either use people…

732
01:03:45,321 --> 01:03:46,405
or end up being used.

733
01:04:42,587 --> 01:04:44,839
She teleports when her heart beats fast.

734
01:04:46,257 --> 01:04:48,050
She doesn't scare easily,

735
01:04:49,468 --> 01:04:50,595
but if she's flustered

736
01:04:51,262 --> 01:04:53,389
or if she's set on doing
or not doing something,

737
01:04:54,223 --> 01:04:57,935
her heart starts to race, driven by
unpredictable emotions and moods,

738
01:04:58,019 --> 01:04:59,353
so don't let your guard down.

739
01:05:00,479 --> 01:05:03,065
She can also teleport objects and people,
so be careful.

740
01:05:03,816 --> 01:05:07,028
Even if she disappears,
she always returns,

741
01:05:07,111 --> 01:05:08,654
but not to the exact same spot.

742
01:05:09,238 --> 01:05:12,325
You should keep watch of the area
and be ready to capture her.

743
01:05:15,620 --> 01:05:17,663
As long as her heart doesn't beat fast,

744
01:05:18,247 --> 01:05:20,041
that woman can't do anything.

745
01:05:40,227 --> 01:05:41,687
What will you do with her now?

746
01:05:43,564 --> 01:05:46,609
Everything has its place and purpose.

747
01:05:47,109 --> 01:05:49,695
That heart doesn't belong to her.

748
01:05:50,196 --> 01:05:51,822
It should be returned to its place.

749
01:05:56,619 --> 01:05:59,163
PERSONAL RECORD CARD
3972

750
01:05:59,246 --> 01:06:01,624
Is there anything else we should know?

751
01:06:02,124 --> 01:06:03,751
Any precautions we should take?

752
01:06:06,295 --> 01:06:07,338
No, there isn't.

753
01:06:37,118 --> 01:06:44,083
OUR MASTER
MAY YOU ALSO MASTER HAPPINESS

754
01:10:09,914 --> 01:10:14,919
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi
